radiographic_examinations.findings: Bilateral lower lobe atelectasis, a 2 mm pulmonary nodule in the left lower lobe unchanged since previous exam. Appendix is fluid filled and dilated up to 11 mm, surrounding small amount of free fluid, and moderate mesenteric fat stranding. No pneumoperitoneum, normal liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, duodenum, or bowel.
